The paper deals with algorithms for listing all maximal cliques in sparse graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also analyzes the performance of the algorithm on a large corpus of real-world graphs, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper mentions that the algorithm has practical applications for analyzing large sparse graphs, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
